/-!
# Small-`t` polynomial bound for the exact truncation

In the regime `1 ≤ t ≤ t0`, we bound the exact truncation `ExactTrunc.ineq2_exact_trunc t` below by
a fixed rational polynomial. This file defines a coefficient function `coeffSmall` and provides an
explicit coefficient list `coeffsSmall` (hard-coded to keep kernel reduction fast), together with
the corresponding polynomial `polySmall`.

## Main definitions
* `coeffSmall`, `coeffsSmall`, `polySmall`

## Main statements
* `coeffsSmall_getD_eq_coeffSmall`
-/

noncomputable section

namespace SpherePacking.Dim24.Ineq2LeOneTruncAux

open AppendixA
open CoeffModel

namespace ExactTruncPosRigorous


/-- Coefficient function defining the small-`t` polynomial lower bound. -/
@[expose] public def coeffSmall (n : ℕ) : ℚ :=
  (A0 n) * (t0Q ^ (2 : ℕ))
    + (B0 n) * invPiLowerQ
    + (C0 n) * CinvBoundQ n

